  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2026-04-20",
    "date": "2026-04-24T17:54:21Z",
    "text": "This bill authorizes the Capitol Police Board to waive the mandatory retirement age for members of the Capitol Police up to age 65. (Under current law, a member of the Capitol Police is generally subject to mandatory retirement\u00a0at age 57 but may receive a waiver from the board authorizing later retirement up to age 60.)\u00a0"
  },
